radiographic_examinations.findings: Extensive soft tissue inflammation extending from the left lateral chest wall to the hand, but no bone involvement, soft tissue gas or fluid collection, or mass lesion.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Decreased edema and central necrosis at the wound site over following days.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Diffuse inflammation without abscess and minimal axillary lymphadenopathy.
